Example:
Mike: Did you know that the author of the book, “Logically Fallacious,” made a fortune on the Internet? Jon: So? Mike: That means that this book must be awesome!

LLM:
#classification: Genetic Fallacy#
For Genetic Fallacy:
Step 1 evaluation: Yes - The argument is evaluating the claim that the book is awesome (its truth value)
Step 2 evaluation: Yes - The argument focuses on the origin/source of the claim (the author made a fortune on the Internet)
Step 3 evaluation: Yes - The conclusion about the book being awesome is based solely on information about the author's financial success
Step 4 evaluation: No - The author's financial success from the Internet is not relevant to determining whether the book is actually awesome
Step 5 evaluation: Yes - The argument follows the pattern: 'This book comes from [successful author], therefore it is awesome'
