Example:
Based on a survey of 1000 American homeowners, 99% of those surveyed have two or more automobiles worth on average $100,000 each.  Therefore, Americans are very wealthy.

LLM:
#classification: Biased Sample Fallacy#
For Biased Sample Fallacy:
Step 1 evaluation: Yes - A population (American homeowners) is being sampled with 1000 respondents
Step 2 evaluation: Yes - The sampled population is being used to draw conclusions about a larger population (all Americans)
Step 3 evaluation: No - The sample population was not carefully chosen to be representative of the larger population (homeowners are not representative of all Americans)
Step 4 evaluation: Yes - The conclusion contains a possible bias in the sample that does not exist in the larger population (homeowners are likely wealthier than the general American population)
Pattern comparison: My answers [Y/Y/N/Y] exactly match ground truth [Y/Y/N/Y]
