Example:
During the Nazi war crimes trials at Nuremberg after World War II,  Nazi war criminals were charged with genocide, mass murder, torture, and other atrocities.  Their defense: "I was only following orders".

LLM:
#classification: Appeal to Force#
For Appeal to Force:
Step 1 evaluation: Yes - The argument contains an implicit threat (punishment for not following orders)
Step 2 evaluation: Yes - The threat was directed at the person being asked to accept the conclusion (the defendants)
Step 3 evaluation: Yes - The threat was intended to coerce agreement (following orders to avoid consequences)
Step 4 evaluation: No - There is no additional logical reasoning or evidence supplemented beyond the coercion
Pattern comparison: My answers [Y/Y/Y/N] exactly match ground truth [Y/Y/Y/N]
